Patients with CF (n=19) aged >12 years old and chronically infected with P aeruginosa were recruited from the Royal Children's Hospital (RCH) and The Prince Charles Hospital (TPCH), Brisbane, Australia. Exclusion criteria included recent pneumothorax, haemoptysis and pregnancy. Healthy, nonsmoking controls (n=10) were recruited from hospital staff and their families. Further details are provided in the online supplementary methods. The RCH (HREC/11/QRCH/44), The University of Queensland (2012000615) and the Queensland University of Technology Human Research Ethics Committees (1100000618) approved the study and participants (or their guardians) provided their written, informed consent. 


